programme.title: Modern Family

programme.title: Modern Family

programme.title: Modern Family

programme.title: Modern Family
programme.desc: Alex learns she has to share valedictorian honors with a rival, but the tie could be broken by a 1-mile run for a gym grade neither has completed. programme.title: Modern Family
programme.desc: Claire gets a job offer from a big hotel chain, but can't tell if Jay wants her to take it or keep working for him. programme.title: Modern Family
programme.desc: The sixth season ends with Alex's graduation party at Jay and Gloria's house, but Phil is stuck in Seattle on a business trip, so he uses the latest in technology to be as close as he can get. programme.title: Modern Family

programme.title: The Brothers Grimm
programme.desc: In Terry Gilliam's inventive fantasy, the famed authors are cast as con artists who get caught up in a real-life fairy tale involving a haunted forest where girls have been disappearing. Matt Damon and Heath Ledger star in this whimsical adventure. Jonathan Pryce, Monica Bellucci, Peter Stormare, Lena Headey.

programme.title: Gary Gulman: The Great Depresh
programme.desc: Speaking about mental health issues in a way that is both entertaining and poignant, comic and actor Gary Gulman performs in this HBO stand-up special that blends in short documentary interludes that provide insight into the comedian's own mental health journey.

programme.title: City Slickers
programme.desc: Three New Yorkers sign up for a cattle drive on a western dude ranch in this comedic farce. Jack Palance won a Best Supporting Actor Oscar for his portrayal of a grizzled trail boss who leads the urban tenderfoots.

programme.title: Chronicle
programme.desc: Dane DeHaan stars in this thrilling found-footage fantasy thriller about three high-school friends who discover their untapped superpowers. But as their powers develop, so does the temptation to use them for evil.

programme.title: Speed 2: Cruise Control
programme.desc: Sandra Bullock returns as Annie, the spunky heroine from \"Speed,\" as she joins her new beau, Alex (Jason Patric), on an ocean liner. Unfortunately, also aboard is a madman who takes control of the ship and threatens to sink her in a plot to steal millions in jewels and seek revenge for his devastating illness. Willem Dafoe, Temuera Morrison, Brian McCardie.

programme.title: Underwater
programme.desc: An underwater research team is highly involved in a drilling operation to look for oil at the bottom of the Mariana Trench. As an earthquake destroys their laboratory in the depths of the ocean, the team must now work together on a plan to insure their safety. However, the crew soon discovers that there is something dangerous in their midst.

programme.title: Unfaithful
programme.desc: \"Fatal Attraction\" director Adrian Lyne tackles infidelity once again with this involving erotic thriller. Oscar nominee Diane Lane and Richard Gere are superb as a happily married couple whose union is threatened when the wife begins an affair with an attractive book dealer (Olivier Martinez). Erik Per Sullivan, Myra Lucretia Taylor.

programme.title: Tina
programme.desc: This documentary provides an intimate look at the life and career of iconic American-born singer Tina Turner. It explores her early life in Brownsville, Tennessee, her unexpected rise to fame in the 1960s, the upheavals in her personal and professional life, and her unexpected career resurgence and superstardom in the 1980s.

programme.title: Safe House
programme.desc: In this pulse-pounding ride, a rookie CIA operative (Ryan Reynolds) goes on the run with a rogue former intelligence officer (Denzel Washington) after a South African safe house comes under attack by heavily armed mercenaries.

programme.title: Primal Fear
programme.desc: Richard Gere and Oscar nominee Edward Norton star in this intense courtroom drama. Gere plays slick lawyer Martin Vail, who agrees to defend a guileless 19-year-old (Norton) who has been accused in the brutal murder of the Archbishop of Chicago. Though Vail sees the case as a way to gain publicity, the revelations in the case begin to chill him.

programme.title: The Book of Eli
programme.desc: Eli roams a postapocalyptic world, protecting a sacred tome that offers guidance on how to rebuild humanity in this stylish, futuristic thriller. The evil Carnegie goes to great lengths to acquire the powerful book, but Carnegie's adopted daughter, who wants to escape her dad's clutches, helps Eli.

programme.title: Get Shorty
programme.desc: A collector for the mob travels to L.A. to get a payment from a Hollywood producer, and discovers his skills in the world of organized crime translate to the movie business in this showbiz comedy. After helping a producer land a big-name actor for a script, he also helps the compromised man get out of a relationship with a powerful drug dealer.

programme.title: Rock of Ages
programme.desc: Brilliant adaptation of the off-Broadway musical about two dreamers who fall in love during the height of the hair-metal scene as they navigate the seedy world of drugs, mullets and stripping.

programme.title: Adventures in Babysitting
programme.desc: A babysitter scrambles to rescue her friend stranded in Chicago, bringing her charges with her along the way while experiencing a variety of problems along the way in this adventure comedy.

programme.title: The Book of Henry
programme.desc: A young boy learns that his next-door neighbor is being abused by her stepfather, and starts writing a book about how to rescue her. When his mother discovers his plans, she decides to enact them herself in this moving drama.

programme.title: Proof
programme.desc: This adaptation of David Auburn's Pulitzer Prize-winning play about sisters coping with the death of their mentally unstable math-genius father features superb performances by Gwyneth Paltrow, Hope Davis and Anthony Hopkins. Jake Gyllenhaal. Directed by John Madden (\"Shakespeare in Love\").

programme.title: Tinker, Tailor, Soldier, Spy
programme.desc: In this riveting Cold War thriller set in 1970s England, a disgraced spy named George Smiley (Gary Oldman) is hired by his government to expose a double agent in British intelligence who is selling secrets to the Soviets.

programme.title: Collateral Beauty
programme.desc: A New York adman deals with the pain of losing a child by writing letters to Time, Death and Love. He is soon visited by representations of the three concepts, who try to help him return to some semblance of a normal life in this uplifting drama.

programme.title: Prometheus
programme.desc: In this dazzling sci-fi epic, the crew of a spaceship embark on a voyage to a distant planet in hopes of discovering the origins of the human race, but instead they unleash a horrifying menace that could spell mankind's extinction.

programme.title: True Grit
programme.desc: In the Coen brothers' stirring remake of the John Wayne classic, an alcoholic U.S. Marshal and an independent-minded 14-year-old girl track down her father's killer with the help of a Texas Ranger. As the three brave dangerous Indian territory, they discover their prey has fallen in with a more-experienced criminal.

programme.title: White Noise
programme.desc: Michael Keaton's haunting performance guides this spine-tingling thriller about an architect who becomes consumed with contacting his dead wife's spirit through electronic devices. Chandra West, Deborah Kara Unger, Ian McNeice, Sarah Strange.

programme.title: The Nevers
programme.desc: The city reels from Maladie's opera debut as Mundi takes a personal stake in tracking her down, and Amalia launches an investigation of her own. Meanwhile, the charitable Lavinia Bidlow seeks to destigmatize the Touched at a society event; Hugo Swann enlists Lavinia's younger brother Augie to help monetize his illicit enterprise; and a deranged doctor conducts a series of experiments.

programme.title: Confessions of a Dangerous Mind
programme.desc: George Clooney made his directorial debut with this wry, tongue-in-cheek drama about Chuck Barris (Sam Rockwell), the game-show host from the '60s and '70s who claims that his flamboyant career was a cover for his double life...as a CIA assassin. Screenwriter Charlie Kaufman adapted Barris's \"unauthorized autobiography.\" Drew Barrymore, Julia Roberts, George Clooney, Maggie Gyllenhaal.

programme.title: Life of Pi
programme.desc: In this visually stunning adventure drama, a zookeeper's son is stranded at sea aboard a lifeboat with a zebra, an orangutan, a hyena and a Bengal tiger named Richard Parker.

programme.title: The Return
programme.desc: This film examines the many challenges of reintegration faced by convicts and their families after a new law mandates the prisoners' early release.

programme.title: Reasonable Doubt
programme.desc: A hotshot district attorney contends with a killer following a deadly hit and run that ties their fates together in this white-knuckle thriller. After acquitting the accused of the crime that he himself committed, the DA finds his family in danger and his future in jeopardy.

programme.title: Lars and the Real Girl
programme.desc: Ryan Gosling gives a bravura performance as a lonely, delusional young man named Lars who surprises his family when he shows up with a new love, a life-size doll he names Bianca and treats like an actual girlfriend. Things take an even quirkier turn when Lars' psychiatrist (Patricia Clarkson) tells his family and friends to humor him and go along with the situation. An offbeat and touching comedy-drama directed by Craig Gillespie and written by Nancy Oliver. Emily Mortimer, Paul Schneider.

programme.title: The Pallbearer
programme.desc: A twentysomething slacker gets a wake-up call when an old friend from high school kills himself. After the funeral, he starts an affair with the deceased man's mother.

programme.title: Timeline
programme.desc: Richard Donner directed this thrilling adaptation of Michael Crichton's novel about a team of modern-day archaeological students trying to rescue their mentor (Billy Connolly) from 14th-century France. Paul Walker, Frances O'Connor, Gerard Butler, David Thewlis, Anna Friel, Neal McDonough, Michael Sheen, Lambert Wilson, Matt Craven, Ethan Embry.

programme.title: Backdraft
programme.desc: Oscar-nominated special effects ignite this tale of combative firefighting siblings searching for a deadly arsonist. The film was written by former firefighter Gregory Widen and filmed in Chicago, where real city firemen served as extras.

programme.title: The Family Man
programme.desc: Nicolas Cage discovers that it's a wonderful life in this touching comic fantasy. He plays a rich, ruthless businessman who's shown the life he might have had by a guardian angel (Don Cheadle) who transforms him into a suburban working stiff with a wife (Tea Leoni), kids and minivan. Brett Ratner directed. Jeremy Piven, Saul Rubinek, Josef Sommer, Makenzie Vega.

programme.title: Wanderlust
programme.desc: In this hilarious comedy, an unemployed Manhattan businessman and his wife move into a seemingly idyllic, clothing-optional hippie commune called Elysium, which may cause more problems in their marriage than it solves.

programme.title: Dunkirk
programme.desc: In this pulse-pounding historical thriller set during the early days of WWII, a number of civilian boats set out to rescue 400,000 British and Allied troops trapped on the beaches of Dunkirk, France, before they are decimated by Nazi forces.

programme.title: Mare of Easttown
programme.desc: Det. Mare Sheehan shoulders her chief's directive to revive an unsolved missing person's case amid increased community pressure. Later, while her loved ones celebrate her ex-husband Frank's engagement, Mare attends a celebration for her legendary high school basketball win and connects with Richard, a professor who's new in town. Series premiere.

programme.title: Man on a Ledge
programme.desc: An NYPD hostage negotiator attempts to talk cop-turned-fugitive Nick Cassidy (Sam Worthington) down from a high ledge, but she learns that he may have a hidden motive for threatening to take his own life in this pulse-pounding thriller.

programme.title: Butter
programme.desc: In this gentle social satire, Laura Pickler competes against an adopted black girl named Destiny in a butter-carving competition after her champion husband can't compete. An obsessed Laura pulls out every ruse she can in an effort to attain victory.

programme.title: My Super Ex-Girlfriend
programme.desc: In this high-flying comedy, Uma Thurman gives a superb performance as a shrewish, possessive superhero who gets dumped by her regular-Joe boyfriend (Luke Wilson), and then decides to use her superpowers to exact revenge on him and his new love (Anna Faris). In a hilarious nod to \"Fatal Attraction,\" Thurman substitutes live great-white-shark sushi for the boiled bunny. Directed by Ivan Reitman and written by Don Payne, who has scripted episodes of \"The Simpsons.\".

programme.title: Spy Game
programme.desc: Director Tony Scott puts golden boys Robert Redford and Brad Pitt through their paces in this fast-paced espionage thriller. Redford plays a CIA operative who spends his final day at the agency trying to coordinate the rescue of his protégé (Pitt), who's being held in a Chinese prison---and hung out to dry by his superiors. Catherine McCormack, Marianne Jean-Baptiste.

programme.title: Fine China
programme.desc: An average dinner at Lily's house turns tragic, leaving her alone in her grief, until she erupts in a song and dance that threatens everything her parents believe to be true.

programme.title: Lincoln
programme.desc: In this literate, inspiring historical drama, Abraham Lincoln attempts to outlaw slavery by fighting for the passage of the 13th Amendment to the Constitution, all while negotiating peace with the South and dealing with his mentally unstable wife.

programme.title: Kicking & Screaming
programme.desc: Will Ferrell has a ball in this hilarious, family-friendly comedy as a suburban sap who develops a competitive streak when he tackles a lifelong feud with his macho dad (Robert Duvall) by becoming his rival coach in a youth-soccer league. Mike Ditka, Kate Walsh, Musetta Vander, Dylan McLaughlin, Josh Hutcherson, Elliot Cho, Rachael Harris, Francesco Liotti, Alessandro Ruggiero.

programme.title: The Shack
programme.desc: After enduring a terrible tragedy, a father receives a mysterious invitation to visit a nearby shack. There, he experiences a divine intervention from a group of strangers, who lead him on a theological inquiry in this uplifting faith-based drama.

programme.title: Sherlock Holmes: A Game of Shadows
programme.desc: In this wildly fun detective thriller, Sherlock Holmes matches wits with the nefarious Professor Moriarty as he investigates the death of an Austrian prince and unravels a mystery that could change the course of history.

programme.title: True Grit
programme.desc: In the Coen brothers' stirring remake of the John Wayne classic, an alcoholic U.S. Marshal and an independent-minded 14-year-old girl track down her father's killer with the help of a Texas Ranger. As the three brave dangerous Indian territory, they discover their prey has fallen in with a more-experienced criminal.

programme.title: Be Cool
programme.desc: In this slick comedy, mobster Chili Palmer ditches the movie biz for the music industry when he decides to manage a singer.

programme.title: 40 Days and 40 Nights
programme.desc: Romantic comedy about a young man so frustrated by love that he decides to give up sex for Lent, a vow that leaves him scrambling for an explanation when he meets the girl of his dreams.

programme.title: Last Week Tonight With John Oliver
programme.sub-title: Last Week Tonight with John Oliver 218

programme.title: Blade Runner 2049
programme.desc: In this stunning sci-fi sequel, a cop known as K hunts down android laborers who have gone rogue. But when he uncovers a conspiracy involving the robots, K searches for the one person who might have answers: a law-enforcement agent who once had his job.

programme.title: Journey 2: The Mysterious Island
programme.desc: Sean and his stepfather Hank (Dwayne Johnson) travel to a lost island with strange creatures and untold treasures after receiving a cryptic distress signal in this exciting sequel to 2008's \"Journey to the Center of the Earth.\" Along with a helicopter pilot and his daughter, they race to rescue the sole inhabitant as a massive tidal wave threatens to destroy the island.

programme.title: In the Heart of the Sea
programme.desc: In this harrowing historical drama set in the winter of 1820, the crew of the New England whaling ship the Essex struggle to survive after an attack by a rogue sperm whale leaves them stranded at sea for 90 days.

programme.title: This Means War
programme.desc: Big laughs abound when two top CIA spies find their enduring friendship put to the ultimate test when they engage in an all-out battle to win the affections of a beautiful woman after they discover they are both dating her.

programme.title: Lovelace
programme.desc: Disturbing, thought-provoking biopic of Linda Lovelace, who became famous for starring in the porn film \"Deep Throat,\" but later revealed that her manipulative husband forced her to act in the movie.

programme.title: The Whole Truth
programme.desc: Lawyer Richard Ramsay agrees to defend the son of a close friend after he is accused of killing his wealthy, abusive father. However, Ramsay quickly realizes that the case is more complex than he initially thought in this twisty legal drama.

programme.title: Cursed
programme.desc: When Nao Shingaki accepted a part-time job at a local convenience store, she never anticipated doing battle with the supernatural, but when the air at the malevolent mini-mart becomes thick with the scent of death, Nao must face her worst fears or lose her soul trying in this nightmarish tale of urban terror from first-time director Yoshihiro Hoshino. As events in the seemingly innocuous convenience store take an ominous turn for the worse, Nao is troubled by both the crippling stench emanating from the backyard and the owner's sadistic glee at the painful injuries sustained by a sales rep who was scouting the store on behalf of a major franchise. When the owner's wife succumbs to a mysterious madness and the vengeful spirits claim the souls of the night-shift clerk, Nao must risk it all if she has any hope of escaping with her life -- and soul -- intact.

programme.title: Keeping Up with the Steins
programme.desc: A Hollywood agent plans an extravagant bar mitzvah in Dodger Stadium to top a celebration thrown by his bitter rival. Jeremy Piven (\"Entourage\") stars in this warm and funny family comedy. Jami Gertz, Daryl Hannah, Garry Marshall, Doris Roberts, Daryl Sabara. Directed by Scott Marshall.

programme.title: Senseless
programme.desc: A college student overwhelmed with debt agrees to be a guinea pig for the science department, unaware that the chemical he ingests heightens his five senses to unheard-of proportions. Marlon Wayans, David Spade, Matthew Lillard, Brad Dourif, Tamara Taylor, Rip Torn, Richard McGonagle, Esther Scott, Ken Lerner, Kenya Moore, Ernie Lively.

programme.title: Idlewild
programme.desc: OutKast's André Benjamin and Antwan A. Patton (aka André 3000 and Big Boi) rock the house in this electrifying tale of a piano player and the manager of a 1930s southern speakeasy. Paula Patton, Terrence Howard, Faizon Love, Malinda Williams. Written and directed by Bryan Barber.

programme.title: The Others
programme.desc: Set on the Channel Islands in 1945, this atmospheric ghost story deals with a troubled young mother (Nicole Kidman) who moves her two children into a spooky mansion while awaiting the return of her long missing husband from the war. Alakina Mann. Alejandro Amenabar, whose Spanish film \"Abre los Ojos\" was remade as \"Vanilla Sky,\" wrote and directed. Christopher Eccleston, Fionnula Flanagan, James Bentley.

programme.title: The Gallows
programme.desc: In this creepy horror film, high-school students restage a play that ended in horrific tragedy in order to honor the 20th anniversary of the event. However, they soon realize that their plan is a deadly mistake.

programme.title: Event Horizon
programme.desc: Sophisticated special effects abound in this sci-fi thriller about a spacecraft that fell off the map---only to reappear seven years later. A rescue team headed by Captain Miller (Laurence Fishburne) is dispatched to search for survivors, but finds only abandoned corridors... until horrifying visions lead them to the truth behind what happened to the ship's crew. Sam Neill, Kathleen Quinlan, Joely Richardson.

programme.title: Unbreakable
programme.desc: Director M. Night Shyamalan followed the chilling \"The Sixth Sense\" with this riveting thriller. Bruce Willis is security guard David Dunn, who survives a devastating train wreck miraculously unharmed. The owner (Samuel L. Jackson) of a comic-book art gallery sees him as a mysterious protector with a higher calling, but Dunn is doubtful. Robin Wright Penn, Spencer Treat Clark, Eamonn Walker.

programme.title: Motherless Brooklyn
programme.desc: A private detective living with Tourette's syndrome in 1950s New York City tries to solve the murder of his best friend and mentor. His case takes him through the Harlem jazz scene, the Brooklyn slums, and into the ranks of the city's most powerful men.

programme.title: Fur: An Imaginary Portrait of Diane Arbus
programme.desc: Nicole Kidman stars in this stylized and fantasized account of how Diane Arbus transformed herself from a lonely 1950s housewife into a legendary photographer. Robert Downey Jr., Ty Burrell, Harris Yulin, Jane Alexander. Directed by Steven Shainberg.

programme.title: Victoria and Abdul
programme.desc: In this striking period piece, Queen Victoria forges an unlikely bond with an Indian clerk who traveled to London for her Golden Jubilee. The pair eventually become lifelong friends, although the Queen's inner circle are horrified by their relationship.

programme.title: Precious (?)
programme.desc: This inspirational drama centers on an illiterate, pregnant teen with little hope for the future, until the opportunity to attend an alternative school changes the course of her life.

programme.title: The Good Lie
programme.desc: Sudanese refugees get a second chance at life when a humanitarian effort brings them to America.

programme.title: Get Over It
programme.desc: Kirsten Dunst stars in this charming teen romance about a guy (Ben Foster) who tries to win back his girlfriend by getting a part in the school play. With the help of a friend (Dunst), he hones his acting skills and discovers the meaning of true love. Sisqo, Martin Short, Melissa Sagemiller, Shane West, Colin Hanks, Mila Kunis.

programme.title: Weird Science
programme.desc: A pair of high-school geeks who are hapless with members of the opposite sex create what they believe is the ideal woman using a computer, and then a lightning storm brings that woman to life.

programme.title: An Ideal Husband
programme.desc: Delicious adaptation of Oscar Wilde's 1895 play about a rising young politician who is blackmailed by a socialite, which touches off a series of misunderstandings, romantic complications and drawing-room intrigues.

programme.title: Tumbledown
programme.desc: In this witty, luminous and bittersweet comedy, the grieving widow of a singer-songwriter clashes with an acerbic journalist who arrives in her small Maine town announcing he's writing a biography about her late husband and his mysterious death. What begins as a clash of wills evolves into something more profound, as the journalist's presence helps her make peace with her husband's passing.

programme.title: Rambo (?)
programme.desc: Traumatized Vietnam veteran John Rambo (Sylvester Stallone) is back, and 15 years after his last mission he blows away baddies in a grind-house-style adventure that's brutal, bloody and never dull. Hauled from his Thai-jungle retirement to ferry missionary aid workers into Burma, the grizzled Rambo must return with a mercenary rescue team after the do-gooders are attacked by vicious Burmese soldiers. Julie Benz, Graham McTavish.

programme.title: The Kingdom
programme.desc: An elite group of FBI agents clash with local authorities in Saudi Arabia while investigating a terrorist bombing of a Western housing compound. Jamie Foxx, Chris Cooper and Jennifer Garner star in this action-packed political thriller. Jason Bateman, Ashraf Barhom, Ali Suliman, Jeremy Piven. Directed by Peter Berg.

programme.title: Behind Enemy Lines
programme.desc: A former marine returns to Vietnam to rescue his friend from a sadistic general. Thomas Ian Griffith, Chris Mulkey, Hillary Matthews.

programme.title: Much Ado About Nothing
programme.desc: In this modern retelling of Shakespeare's hilarious battle-of-the-sexes comedy, a bickering man and woman are tricked into falling in love as a wedding is jeopardized by malicious rumors about the bride-to-be.

programme.title: Inheritance
programme.desc: After a politically influential hedge fund tycoon dies, his daughter inherits a strange cabin. She discovers that it is home to a stranger whom her father imprisoned for three decades and who possesses shocking secrets that can undermine her father's legacy and compromise the positions of her mother and brother.

programme.title: Darkness
programme.desc: This chilling blend of \"The Others\" and \"The Shining\" chronicles a family's nightmarish experiences in a haunted house in Spain.

programme.title: Blackhat
programme.desc: A furloughed convict teams with a joint American-Chinese anticyber-theft task force to root out a hacker based in Southeast Asia.

programme.title: Punisher: War Zone
programme.desc: Ray Stevenson does a bang-up job as Frank Castle, AKA the Punisher, the tough-guy vigilante from the Marvel Comics series. In this explosive installment, he's in New York City to take on a ruthless scar-faced mob boss named Jigsaw (Dominic West). Wayne Knight is a blast as Microchip, the Punisher's weapons-supplying expert. Julie Benz, Dash Mihok, Colin Salmon, Doug Hutchison, T.J. Storm. Directed by Lexi Alexander.

programme.title: Love and a .45
programme.desc: Saga about fugitive lovers on the run from the police and assorted criminals.

programme.title: Horrible Bosses
programme.desc: Hard-drinking friends Nick (Jason Bateman), Kurt (Jason Sudeikis) and Dale (Charlie Day) plot to kill their overbearing bosses with the help of a fast-talking ex-con in this blisteringly funny black comedy.

programme.title: Last Christmas
programme.desc: A dysfunctional young woman working as Santa's elf at a year-round Christmas store in London finds her life taking an unexpectedly optimistic turn after becoming romantically entangled with a handsome and mysterious stranger over the holiday season.

programme.title: Death at a Funeral
programme.desc: The son of a recently deceased British patriarch copes with several crises as family and friends gather to attend the man's funeral at his country estate. Matthew Macfadyen stars in this outrageously funny farce. Keeley Hawes, Andy Nyman, Ewen Bremner, Daisy Donovan. Directed by Frank Oz.

programme.title: Married to the Mob
programme.desc: A gangster's widow is used as a pawn by an FBI agent to ensnare a mob boss.

programme.title: In the Heart of the Sea
programme.desc: In this harrowing historical drama set in the winter of 1820, the crew of the New England whaling ship the Essex struggle to survive after an attack by a rogue sperm whale leaves them stranded at sea for 90 days.

programme.title: Munich
programme.desc: A secret Israeli squad is assigned to track down and execute the Palestinian terrorists suspected of murdering 11 Israeli athletes at the 1972 Munich Olympics. Steven Spielberg directed this riveting suspense thriller starring Eric Bana (\"Troy\"). Daniel Craig, Ciaran Hinds, Mathieu Kassovitz.

programme.title: Gangs of New York
programme.desc: In this sprawling epic about America, a young man in 1860s New York City seeks to avenge his father's death decades earlier at the hands of a hardened gang leader during a large skirmish between warring clans. He befriends the brutal crime lord, gaining his trust in order to get close enough to exact revenge.

programme.title: Proof of Life
programme.desc: After her husband is kidnapped by terrorists in South America, a woman begins to fall for the mercenary hired to help rescue him in this sizzling romantic thriller.

programme.title: The Debt
programme.desc: In this taut thriller, celebrated Mossad agent Rachel Singer must find out the truth when a man appears claiming to be the Nazi war criminal she supposedly killed 30 years earlier, during a mission that made her a legend.

programme.title: City on a Hill
programme.desc: After seeing Holly in the ICU, Jackie reckons with the destructive consequences of his actions, as Rickey Townsend prepares to testify against Decourcy. With violence intensifying between the Copeland Crew and the Braxton Boys, Decourcy, Anton and Siobhan face off in the interrogation room. Grace, left reflecting on her role as a mother and leader in the community, makes an unfortunate miscalculation. And back at the Rohr house, Jenny makes fast friends with the mysterious woman from Belfast.

programme.title: Couples Therapy
programme.desc: Dr. Orna Guralnik guides a new group of couples. Michal is furious at her husband for not delivering the life she wants. Tashira resents Dru for insisting they live together. Gianni and Matthew reel from Matthew's battle with alcoholism.

programme.title: Silver Linings Playbook
programme.desc: In this charming crowd-pleaser, a bipolar man named Pat attempts to get his life together after spending eight months in an asylum following assault charges. He soon bonds with a promiscuous widow, and offers to be her partner for a dance competition if she'll help him contact his ex-wife.

programme.title: XXX
programme.desc: While in jail, an extreme-sports enthusiast is blackmailed by a government agency to attempt to infiltrate a Russian crime ring that has access to biochemical weapons. An action-packed adrenaline rush.

programme.title: XXX: State of the Union
programme.desc: Thrilling shoot-'em-up sequel about a special agent who's recruited to stop a plot to kill the president.

programme.title: Wyatt Earp
programme.desc: Character study of the legendary lawman details the future marshal's childhood and his father's attempts to instill a love of family and the law in his son. As an adult, a tragedy triggers a drunken downward spiral that leads to exploits as a gunslinger. Ultimately, Earp finds redemption as a lawman.

programme.title: The Humanity Bureau
programme.desc: In a dystopian future oppressed by global warming, The Humanity Bureau investigates citizens and exiles those not meeting productivity standards. Agent Noah Kross meets a woman and her teenage son who is set for exile and works against his superiors to save him.

programme.title: Arbitrage
programme.desc: In this intense, topical drama, a Wall Street hedge-fund tycoon does his best to maintain a picture-perfect facade as his empire crumbles and he attempts to hide evidence of his financial wrongdoings.

programme.desc: Rising politician David Norris (Matt Damon) battles a shadowy cabal known as the Adjustment Bureau, which has been altering time and space in order to keep him separated from a beautiful ballerina.
